  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Feature or Bug? i.e Type: Bug)\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Describe the feature you would like, or briefly summarise the bug and what you did, what you expected to happen, and what actually happens. Sections below)\r\n*Summary*: If name contains emoji then emoji's picture is cut on Chats, View Profile and Contacts screens. In addition, on Chats screen bottom of the text is also cut if Display name contains emoji.\r\n![chats - emoji in name](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/6584810/24343694/16d68f2e-12c8-11e7-82f7-2ad647c02424.jpg)\r\n![profile - emoji in name](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/6584810/24343698/199eed28-12c8-11e7-9a09-bd3357a743d8.jpg)\r\n![contacts - emoji in name](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/6584810/24343691/1186d376-12c8-11e7-91ab-1069d897665d.jpg)\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n[comment]: # (Describe what you expected to happen.)\r\nEmoji is fully visible in Contact name on all screens\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n[comment]: # (Describe what actually happened.)\r\nEmoji picture is cut on  Chats, View Profile and Contacts\r\n### Reproduction\r\n[comment]: # (Describe how we can replicate the bug step by step.)\r\nSeems to be issue only for iOS. Was working fine in 0.9.4 build. \r\nfrom Android:\r\n- Open Status and login\r\n- Change your display name, so it contains some emoji\r\n- Write a message to iOS contact from your contacts\r\nfrom iOS:\r\n- Open Profile screen of your Android contact (in 1-1 chat tap on user picture) \r\n- View  a message from some of your Android contacts with emoji in name and use that contact's account to see how your display name is shown on Chats and in Contacts\r\n\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n[comment]: # (Please do your best to fill this out.)\r\n* Status version: bug/new-member-to-group-ui-refresh-943 (iOS) https://i.diawi.com/Y3pRDJ\r\n* Operating System: iOS\r\n\r\n",
